Verisk Analytics, Inc. (VRSK) Shares Bought by Bares Capital Management Inc.

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Bares Capital Management Inc. raised its position in Verisk Analytics, Inc. (NASDAQ:VRSK) by 16.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the SEC. The firm owned 1,221,990 shares of the business services provider’s stock after buying an additional 169,923 shares during the period. Verisk Analytics makes up about 4.9% of Bares Capital Management Inc.’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 13th largest position. Bares Capital Management Inc. owned 0.74% of Verisk Analytics worth $99,152,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds have also bought and sold shares of the company. Ledyard National Bank boosted its position in shares of Verisk Analytics by 40.4% in the first quarter. Ledyard National Bank now owns 2,085 shares of the business services provider’s stock valued at $169,000 after buying an additional 600 shares in the last quarter. Pacad Investment Ltd. acquired a new position in shares of Verisk Analytics during the fourth quarter valued at $211,000. Weatherstone Capital Management boosted its position in shares of Verisk Analytics by 5.3% in the first quarter. Weatherstone Capital Management now owns 2,818 shares of the business services provider’s stock valued at $229,000 after buying an additional 142 shares in the last quarter. Conning Inc. boosted its position in shares of Verisk Analytics by 3.1% in the first quarter. Conning Inc. now owns 2,990 shares of the business services provider’s stock valued at $243,000 after buying an additional 90 shares in the last quarter. Finally, OppenheimerFunds Inc. boosted its position in shares of Verisk Analytics by 7.9% in the first quarter. OppenheimerFunds Inc. now owns 3,044 shares of the business services provider’s stock valued at $247,000 after buying an additional 222 shares in the last quarter. 92.00% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get Verisk Analytics Inc. alerts:



Shares of Verisk Analytics, Inc. (NASDAQ:VRSK) traded up 0.28% on Friday, hitting $86.51. The company had a trading volume of 881,499 shares. Verisk Analytics, Inc. has a 1-year low of $75.60 and a 1-year high of $87.40. The firm has a market capitalization of $14.30 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 24.31 and a beta of 0.65. The company has a 50 day moving average price of $83.28 and a 200 day moving average price of $81.82. 




Verisk Analytics (NASDAQ:VRSK) last released its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The business services provider reported $0.74 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $0.78 by $0.04. Verisk Analytics had a net margin of 30.29% and a return on equity of 37.52%. The business had revenue of $502.60 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $511.99 million. On average, equities analysts forecast that Verisk Analytics, Inc. will post $3.18 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
